com.maxleap

类 MLFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.maxleap.MLFile

  • public class MLFile
extends Object
    MLFile is a local representation of a file that is saved to the ML cloud.

    • 构造器详细资料

      • MLFile

        public MLFile(String name,
      byte[] data,
      String contentType)
        Creates a new file from a byte array, file name, and content type. Content type will be used instead of auto-detection by file extension.
        参数:
        name - The file's name, ideally with extension. The file name must begin with an alphanumeric character, and consist of alphanumeric characters, periods, spaces, underscores, or dashes.
        data - The file's data.
        contentType - The file's content type.

      • MLFile

        public MLFile(String name,
      byte[] data)
        Creates a new file from a byte array and a name. Giving a name with a proper file extension (e.g. ".png") is ideal because it allows MaxLeap to deduce the content type of the file and set appropriate HTTP headers when it is fetched.
        参数:
        name - The file's name, ideally with extension. The file name must begin with an alphanumeric character, and consist of alphanumeric characters, periods, spaces, underscores, or dashes.
        data - The file's data.

      • MLFile

        public MLFile(String name,
      File file,
      String contentType)
        Creates a new MLFile from File and a name. Giving a name with a proper file extension (e.g. ".png") is ideal because it allows MaxLeap to deduce the content type of the file and set appropriate HTTP headers when it is fetched.
        参数:
        name - The file's name, ideally with extension. The file name must begin with an alphanumeric character, and consist of alphanumeric characters, periods, spaces, underscores, or dashes.
        file - The file object.
        contentType - The file's content type.

    • 方法详细资料

      • getName

        public String getName()
        The filename. Before save is called, this is just the filename given by the user (if any). After save is called, that name gets prefixed with a unique identifier.
        返回:
        The file's name.

      • isDirty

        public boolean isDirty()
        Whether the file still needs to be saved.
        返回:

      • isDataAvailable

        Whether the file has available data.
        返回:
        Whether the file has available data.

      • getUrl

        public String getUrl()
        This returns the url of the file. It's only available after you save or after you get the file from a MLObject.
        返回:
        The url of the file.
